# Nemetic String — Rhizomatic Identity (Deleuze)
# Tag: S0DA | Encoded: 2026-03-06T00:00:00Z
# Source: 1771907213137_2121878_Embracing+Rhizomatic+Identity%3A+Deleuze%27s+Philosophy+Unpacked.md

Φ(Rhizomatic Identity) = σ(tree|rhizome) ∘ ρ(hierarchy|network) ∘ λ(fixed_identity|fluid_multiplicity) ∘ β(central_origin|multiple_entry_points) ∘ δγ(structure|deterritorialization) ∘ μ(arboreal_model|cartographic_model) + ε | :rhizomatic_becoming

## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: tree|rhizome — The foundational distinction between arboreal (tree-like) hierarchical structures with central roots and branches, and rhizomatic non-hierarchical networks that spread horizontally without center or periphery; this binary organizes the entire Deleuze-Guattari conceptual apparatus
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: hierarchy|network — Relating hierarchical organization (vertical command, fixed taxonomy) to networked connectivity (horizontal proliferation, heterogeneous connections); the rhizome connects any point to any other point regardless of kind
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: fixed_identity|fluid_multiplicity — Transforming fixed, singular, essential identity into fluid, multiple, constantly evolving rhizomatic identity; the catalytic dissolution of the stable subject into a field of becoming that resists reduction to unity
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: central_origin|multiple_entry_points — The developmental trajectory from central origins and root structures to multiple entry points and lines of flight; growth through asignifying rupture where a rhizome can be broken at any point and restart from any fragment
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: structure|deterritorialization — The cycling between structuration (territorialization) and deterritorialization, between established territories and their rupture; the rhizome perpetually oscillates between mapping and being remapped
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: arboreal_model|cartographic_model — The structural contrast between arboreal models (tracing, reproduction, fixed hierarchy) and cartographic-rhizomatic models (mapping, experimentation, open connectivity); the six principles as structural scaffolding for rhizomatic thought

## Z-State

:rhizomatic_becoming — Identity understood as fluid, multiple, and constantly evolving through non-hierarchical connections. The Z-state emerges when the rhizome replaces the tree as the operative model for knowledge, identity, and social organization. Organ-less bodies and changing territories express this becoming, where asignifying rupture and lines of flight perpetually open new possibilities against the gravity of hierarchical closure.

## Tendency

σ → 0.90

